	<p>From the information in this table, I suspect that vampires might form social groups - much like covens in popular media. The high concentration of deaths in low populated states like Missouri indicates something more nefarious than the "accidents" that most of these deaths are labeled as. Given the low number of vampires, it would also make sense for groups to form for protection. Perhaps they even form independent communities so to minimize contact with humans outside of a feeding context.</p>

